# to generate the key

```jsx
ssh-keygen -t rsa -b 4096 -C "your_email@eample.com"
```

```jsx
ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C "[your_email@example.com](mailto:your_email@example.com)"
```

---

---

# to read the key

```jsx
cat ~/.ssh/id.rsa.pub
```

---

---

# to get the key in cmd

```jsx
ssh -T git@github.com
```

> `-T` → Disable pseudo-terminal allocation (used because GitHub doesn't give shell access)
>
